New World Wealth has published its latest report on the travelling trends of the wealthy – including the world’s best luxury trains. South Africa stands out in this area with two of the five most popular luxury train services in the world, frequented by the super-wealthy. The famous Blue Train ranks as the fourth most popular luxury train service in 2019, just above the pan-African Rovos Rail’s Pride of Africa journey, ranked as the fifth most popular. Other luxury trains on the list include the Eastern & Oriental Express in Europe, the Royal Scotsman in Scotland, and The Orient Express, in Europe. Eastern & Oriental Express – Singapore, Malaysia and Thailand Price: from $270 per person <img class="size-full wp-image-220505 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/EOE-01.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="500" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/EOE-01.jpg 750w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/EOE-01-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="size-full wp-image-220503 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/EOE-02.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="566" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/EOE-02.jpg 1280w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/EOE-02-300x133.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/EOE-02-768x340.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/EOE-02-1024x453.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/EOE-02-1200x531.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="size-full wp-image-220501 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/EOE-03.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="566" srcset="https://busin